<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="25" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,841,2030]" pageId="6" pageNumber="25">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,286,841,867]" pageId="6" pageNumber="25">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Moderately large species with long paired medial longitudinal yellow vittae on scutum and contrasting yellow pattern on abdomen. Yellow scutellar spines slender and almost horizontal, subscutellum not protrudingg posteriorly. Vein R 
<number box="[581,590,935,949]" pageId="6" pageNumber="25" value="4.0">4</number>
short but present, female tergite 
<number box="[990,1005,919,945]" pageId="6" pageNumber="25" value="3.0">3</number>
with transverse row of spots, male aedeagal complex bipartite.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="8" lastPageNumber="27" pageId="6" pageNumber="25" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,841,2030]" box="[198,971,999,1025]" pageId="6" pageNumber="25">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,351,999,1025]" pageId="6" pageNumber="25">Description.</emphasis>
Male body length 6.0 mm, wing length 5.0–5.5 mm.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,841,2030]" pageId="6" pageNumber="25">
<emphasis box="[197,260,1038,1063]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="25">Head</emphasis>
transversely elliptical in frontal view, shining black, with black hairs; nearly equal width of thorax, 1.2 times broader than high in frontal view and nearly 1.1 times high as long as in profile (without antennae); vertex and ocellar tubercle black, with black hairs; eyes contiguous, dark brown, with dense black hairs. Antenna (
<figureCitation box="[270,360,1154,1180]" captionStart="FIGURES 18 – 24" captionStartId="7.[151,270,1881,1905]" captionTargetBox="[167,1436,358,1854]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[151,1436,351,1855]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 18 – 24. Oxycera signata Brunetti, morphological features. 18, male dorsal view; 19, female dorsal view; 20, male lateral view; 21, female lateral view; 22, male antenna; 23, male head, frontal view; 24, male head, frontal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/191660/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="25">
Fig. 
<number box="[328,360,1154,1180]" pageId="6" pageNumber="25" value="22.0">22</number>
</figureCitation>
) with scape and pedicel dark, apical flagellomere with short black hairs; length of scape nearly equal to that of pedicel; flagellum black, basal 
<number box="[778,792,1192,1218]" pageId="6" pageNumber="25" value="4.0">4</number>
flagellomeres forming an elongate-oval complex, with whitish row of sensillae along distal margin of each flagellomere. Arista black, equal to remain of antenna. Frons and face flat, shining black, nearly bare, each side of face with a white vitta along eyes, consisting of white pubescence and hairs (
<figureCitation box="[488,576,1308,1334]" captionStart="FIGURES 18 – 24" captionStartId="7.[151,270,1881,1905]" captionTargetBox="[167,1436,358,1854]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[151,1436,351,1855]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 18 – 24. Oxycera signata Brunetti, morphological features. 18, male dorsal view; 19, female dorsal view; 20, male lateral view; 21, female lateral view; 22, male antenna; 23, male head, frontal view; 24, male head, frontal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/191660/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="25">
Fig. 
<number box="[543,576,1308,1334]" pageId="6" pageNumber="25" value="23.0">23</number>
</figureCitation>
). Similar white vitta on each side of lower half of occiput. Proboscis pale yellow, with yellow hairs. 
<emphasis box="[470,556,1347,1372]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="25">Thorax</emphasis>
mostly shining black, but with following yellow parts: postpronotal lobe and postalar callus; pair of longitudinal vittae being interrupted at the suture and not quite reaching anterior and hind margin of scutum but nearly connected with yellow postalar calli (
<figureCitation box="[1080,1171,1424,1450]" captionStart="FIGURES 18 – 24" captionStartId="7.[151,270,1881,1905]" captionTargetBox="[167,1436,358,1854]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[151,1436,351,1855]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 18 – 24. Oxycera signata Brunetti, morphological features. 18, male dorsal view; 19, female dorsal view; 20, male lateral view; 21, female lateral view; 22, male antenna; 23, male head, frontal view; 24, male head, frontal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/191660/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="25">
Fig. 
<number box="[1138,1171,1424,1450]" pageId="6" pageNumber="25" value="18.0">18</number>
</figureCitation>
); side of scutum with broad vittae from postpronotal lobe to transverse suture; upper margin of pleura with distinct yellow vitta from postpronotal lobe to wing base (
<figureCitation box="[587,674,1502,1528]" captionStart="FIGURES 18 – 24" captionStartId="7.[151,270,1881,1905]" captionTargetBox="[167,1436,358,1854]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[151,1436,351,1855]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 18 – 24. Oxycera signata Brunetti, morphological features. 18, male dorsal view; 19, female dorsal view; 20, male lateral view; 21, female lateral view; 22, male antenna; 23, male head, frontal view; 24, male head, frontal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/191660/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="25">
Fig. 
<number box="[641,674,1502,1528]" pageId="6" pageNumber="25" value="20.0">20</number>
</figureCitation>
); scutellum mostly yellow, with black posterior margin and a pair of brownish yellow spines. Hairs on thorax pale, but more brownish in front of scutellum and along posterior margin of scutellum. Wings pale brownish, hyaline, veins and stigma brownish yellow. Legs yellow but basal 
<number box="[151,166,1618,1644]" pageId="6" pageNumber="25" value="2.0">2</number>
/ 
<number box="[175,188,1618,1644]" pageId="6" pageNumber="25" value="3.0">3</number>
of femora brown to black and basal half of fore tibia brownish yellow, apical half dark brown; mid tibia brownish yellow; basal and apical parts of hind tibia brownish yellow, middle blackish; fore tarsi black, mid and hind tarsi with bases of tarsomeres 
<number box="[644,691,1695,1721]" pageId="6" pageNumber="25" value="1.5" valueMax="2.0" valueMin="1.0">1–2</number>
brownish yellow, hind 
<number box="[984,1030,1695,1721]" pageId="6" pageNumber="25" value="1.5" valueMax="2.0" valueMin="1.0">1–2</number>
tarsomeres dark to black. Halter yellow. 
<emphasis box="[244,355,1734,1759]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="25">Abdomen</emphasis>
slightly broader than thorax, with following yellow parts on dorsum (
<figureCitation box="[1177,1258,1734,1760]" captionStart="FIGURES 18 – 24" captionStartId="7.[151,270,1881,1905]" captionTargetBox="[167,1436,358,1854]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[151,1436,351,1855]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 18 – 24. Oxycera signata Brunetti, morphological features. 18, male dorsal view; 19, female dorsal view; 20, male lateral view; 21, female lateral view; 22, male antenna; 23, male head, frontal view; 24, male head, frontal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/191660/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="25">
Fig. 
<number box="[1228,1258,1734,1760]" pageId="6" pageNumber="25" value="18.0">18</number>
</figureCitation>
): tergite 
<number box="[1361,1375,1734,1760]" pageId="6" pageNumber="25" value="1.0">1</number>
with a narrow transverse yellow fascia at base; tergite 
<number box="[732,747,1772,1798]" pageId="6" pageNumber="25" value="2.0">2</number>
with narrow yellow lateral margin; tergite 
<number box="[1255,1270,1772,1798]" pageId="6" pageNumber="25" value="3.0">3</number>
with a pair of large angular yellow spot on each side-margin reaching from anterior nearly to posterior margin; tergite 
<number box="[1363,1377,1811,1837]" pageId="6" pageNumber="25" value="4.0">4</number>
with a pair of spots on each side which is smaller than that of tergite 
<number box="[911,928,1850,1876]" pageId="6" pageNumber="25" value="3.0">3</number>
; tergite 
<number box="[1025,1040,1850,1876]" pageId="6" pageNumber="25" value="5.0">5</number>
with a yellow apical spot; venter wholly black. 
<emphasis box="[317,489,1889,1914]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="25">Male genitalia</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[505,646,1888,1914]" captionStart="FIGURES 25 – 27" captionStartId="8.[151,274,814,838]" captionTargetBox="[165,1415,204,758]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[151,1436,194,790]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 25 – 27. Oxycera signata Brunetti, 1920, male terminalia. 25, tergites 9 – 10 and cerci, dorsal view; 26, aedeagal complex, dorsal view; 27, genital capsule, dorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/191661/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="25">
Figs. 
<number box="[571,646,1888,1914]" pageId="6" pageNumber="25" value="26.0" valueMax="27.0" valueMin="25.0">25–27</number>
</figureCitation>
) small; aedeagal complex bipartite, without median tube (
<figureCitation box="[1328,1415,1888,1914]" captionStart="FIGURES 25 – 27" captionStartId="8.[151,274,814,838]" captionTargetBox="[165,1415,204,758]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[151,1436,194,790]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 25 – 27. Oxycera signata Brunetti, 1920, male terminalia. 25, tergites 9 – 10 and cerci, dorsal view; 26, aedeagal complex, dorsal view; 27, genital capsule, dorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/191661/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="25">
Fig. 
<number box="[1382,1415,1888,1914]" pageId="6" pageNumber="25" value="26.0">26</number>
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,841,2030]" lastBlockId="7.[151,1437,152,294]" lastPageId="7" lastPageNumber="26" pageId="6" pageNumber="25">
Female (
<figureCitation box="[301,444,1927,1953]" captionStart="FIGURES 18 – 24" captionStartId="7.[151,270,1881,1905]" captionTargetBox="[167,1436,358,1854]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[151,1436,351,1855]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 18 – 24. Oxycera signata Brunetti, morphological features. 18, male dorsal view; 19, female dorsal view; 20, male lateral view; 21, female lateral view; 22, male antenna; 23, male head, frontal view; 24, male head, frontal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/191660/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="25">
Figs. 
<number box="[367,444,1927,1953]" pageId="6" pageNumber="25" value="19.21">19, 21</number>
</figureCitation>
). Body length 5.5–6.0 mm, wings length 5.0 mm. Similar to male except as follows: Eyes widely separated, with relatively broad postocular band; frons with a pair of yellow longitudinal vittae connecting with white vittae on face (
<figureCitation box="[625,720,2004,2030]" captionStart="FIGURES 18 – 24" captionStartId="7.[151,270,1881,1905]" captionTargetBox="[167,1436,358,1854]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[151,1436,351,1855]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 18 – 24. Oxycera signata Brunetti, morphological features. 18, male dorsal view; 19, female dorsal view; 20, male lateral view; 21, female lateral view; 22, male antenna; 23, male head, frontal view; 24, male head, frontal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/191660/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="25">
Fig. 
<number box="[685,720,2004,2030]" pageId="6" pageNumber="25" value="24.0">24</number>
</figureCitation>
); antenna mostly brownish yellow; scutum with a pair of longitudinal vittae which are interrupted at suture, reaching anterior or hind margin of scutum and connected with yellow postalar calli (
<figureCitation box="[483,575,190,216]" captionStart="FIGURES 18 – 24" captionStartId="7.[151,270,1881,1905]" captionTargetBox="[167,1436,358,1854]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[151,1436,351,1855]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 18 – 24. Oxycera signata Brunetti, morphological features. 18, male dorsal view; 19, female dorsal view; 20, male lateral view; 21, female lateral view; 22, male antenna; 23, male head, frontal view; 24, male head, frontal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/191660/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="26">
Fig. 
<number box="[541,575,190,216]" pageId="7" pageNumber="26" value="19.0">19</number>
</figureCitation>
); color of legs slightly darker than in male; abdominal dorsum with a subquadrate yellow spot in tergite 
<number box="[561,576,229,255]" pageId="7" pageNumber="26" value="1.0">1</number>
and a pair circular spots in middle of tergite 
<number box="[1114,1131,229,255]" pageId="7" pageNumber="26" value="3.0">3</number>
; yellow lateral margin on tergite 
<number box="[232,247,268,294]" pageId="7" pageNumber="26" value="2.0">2</number>
broader than in male (
<figureCitation box="[512,600,268,294]" captionStart="FIGURES 18 – 24" captionStartId="7.[151,270,1881,1905]" captionTargetBox="[167,1436,358,1854]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[151,1436,351,1855]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 18 – 24. Oxycera signata Brunetti, morphological features. 18, male dorsal view; 19, female dorsal view; 20, male lateral view; 21, female lateral view; 22, male antenna; 23, male head, frontal view; 24, male head, frontal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/191660/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="26">
Fig. 
<number box="[567,600,268,294]" pageId="7" pageNumber="26" value="19.0">19</number>
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
