<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,923,1300]" pageId="8" pageNumber="27">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,319,1001,1027]" pageId="8" pageNumber="27">Remarks.</emphasis>
The male of this species may be distinguished by dense hairs on the eyes, and a yellow pattern on thorax and abdomen. The female with a unique colour pattern on tergite 
<number box="[1065,1080,1042,1068]" pageId="8" pageNumber="27" value="3.0">3</number>
is described here for the first time. R. Rozkosny (pers. comm., 
<date box="[572,740,1080,1106]" pageId="8" pageNumber="27" value="2009-05-25">
<number box="[572,603,1080,1106]" pageId="8" pageNumber="27" value="25.0">25</number>
May 
<number box="[676,740,1080,1106]" pageId="8" pageNumber="27" value="2009.0">2009</number>
</date>
